&lt;h3&gt;Before Spring 5.2&lt;/h3&gt;

You can use the `getAnnotations` method to find all non-meta present on the supplied element.

Either get all direct annotations:

```java
var field = ItemDto.class.getField(&quot;text&quot;);
var annotation = AnnotationUtils.getAnnotations(field)[0];

System.out.println(annotation.annotationType().getSimpleName());
```
&gt; ```
&gt; StringDomain
&gt; ```

However, this method is deprecated as of 5.2

&lt;h3&gt;Spring 5.2 and newer&lt;/h3&gt;

The replacement for the deprecated method is MergedAnnotations API ([source][1]). 

```java
var field = ItemDto.class.getField(&quot;text&quot;);
MergedAnnotations.from(field)
        .stream()
        .filter(a -&gt; a.getType().isAssignableFrom(StringDomain.class))
        .findFirst()
        .ifPresent(a -&gt; System.out.println(a.getType().getSimpleName()));

System.out.println(annotations);
```
&gt; ```
&gt; StringDomain
&gt; ```

Or check whether the particular one is present:

```java
var field = ItemDto.class.getField(&quot;text&quot;);
var hasStringDomain = MergedAnnotations.from(field)
    .isDirectlyPresent(StringDomain.class);

System.out.println(hasStringDomain);
```
&gt; ```
&gt; true
&gt; ```


  [1]: http://www.java2s.com/example/java-src/pkg/org/springframework/core/annotation/annotationutils-1c465.html

In the given scenario, since the BaseDomain annotation is used as a meta-annotation (annotation on another annotation), you can determine if the returned BaseDomain annotation is part of StringDomain by checking if the field&#39;s annotation type is annotated with StringDomain. Here&#39;s how you can achieve this:

    final BaseDomain annotation = AnnotationUtils.findAnnotation(field, BaseDomain.class);

    if (annotation != null) {
    Annotation[] annotations = annotation.annotationType().getAnnotations();

    for (Annotation ann : annotations) {
        if (ann.annotationType() == StringDomain.class) {
            // The returned BaseDomain is part of StringDomain
            // Perform the desired processing for StringDomain annotation
            // ...
            break;
        }
    }
}

